  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do you remove your Gmail Profile picture?",
  "response": "To remove your Gmail profile picture, follow these steps:\n\n### On a Computer:\n1. **Open Gmail**: Go to [Gmail](https://mail.google.com/) and log in if you haven\u2019t already.\n2. **Access Google Account Settings**:\n   - Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner of the page.\n   - Select **\"Manage your Google Account\"**.\n3. **Go to Personal Info**:\n   - In the left-hand menu, click on **\"Personal info\"**.\n4. **Edit Profile Picture**:\n   - Scroll down to the **\"Profile\"** section.\n   - Click on your profile picture.\n5. **Remove Picture**:\n   - Click the **\"Remove\"** option (it looks like a trash can icon).\n   - Confirm by clicking **\"Remove\"** again.\n\n### On the Gmail App (Android/iOS):\n1. **Open the Gmail App**: Launch the Gmail app on your device.\n2. **Access Account Settings**:\n   - Tap your profile picture in the top-right corner.\n   - Select **\"Manage your Google Account\"**.\n3. **Go to Personal Info**:\n   - Tap the **\"Personal info\"** tab.\n4. **Edit Profile Picture**:\n   - Scroll to the **\"Profile\"** section and tap your profile picture.\n5. **Remove Picture**:\n   - Tap the **trash can icon** to remove the picture.\n   - Confirm by tapping **\"Remove\"**.\n\nAfter removing your profile picture, it will revert to the default icon with your initials or the first letter of your name.",
